
[1]errand

   ER'RAND, n.

   1. A verbal message; a mandate or order; something to be told or done;
   a communication to be made to some person at a distance. The servant
   was sent on an errand; he told his errand; he has done the errand.
   These are the most common modes of using this word.

   I have a secret errand to thee, O King. Judges 3.

   2. Any special business to be transacted by a messenger.
